<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ozymandia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Would it be a good idea for my 50 druid to carry a stack of peridots for rezz payments?  I ask because I got a rez for a friend in BW the other night and when I went to pay the cleric he said he would accept as much as I offered "because he needs peridots."  Would a lot of clerics accept 4 - 5 peridots in lieu of cash?  Or would it not be worth it to carry the dots?<P>Thanks,<BR>Ozymandia</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">preiter</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Definitely worth it. My monk carries around a stack of peridot, because it's way lighter than cash.<P>I would recommend 10 peridots as a standard rez payment, though.<P>------------------<BR><B>Merpa Gigglesnort, Muerta Bella, Shakah Lakalaka</B><BR>Citizen of the Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Peridots cost 11.5-12.5pp, and I'd say most clerics would be happy to get 5 or so for a rez.  I know I feel guilty taking money when I do a rez, but I'd gladly take something you didn't need and that helps me out.<P>To catch all the suckers I'd try "Hey, I just died and don't have any cash, but I've looted 5 of these peridots this night and I've heard that your spells use them.  I'd gladly give them to you if you could come rez me."</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kimbera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Though only a level 40 cleric, I would not hesitate to say that many (most) clerics would much prefer the peridots over cash.  In fact, I suspect that if you're ever shouting for a rez in a zone, you'd be more likely to get a response by offering 10 peridots than 150 pp.<P>I guess a druidic analogy would be donations for SoW... would you rather have 1 pp offered, or a stack of bat wings (especially when you're running low)?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dannig</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Peridots would stack great in my little boxes   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  Faaaarrrrr less trips to the bank if I received them instead of cash.<P>------------------<BR>Dannig   52 Cleric<BR>Dark Elf <BR>Dark Asylum<BR>http://personal.pitnet.net/asylum/<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I tell everyone who tries to pay for a rez that if they want to compensate a cleric, peridots are the way to do it with class.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Jubal:<BR><B>I tell everyone who tries to pay for a rez that if they want to compensate a cleric, peridots are the way to do it with class.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Aye - Peridot payment are definately cool.<P>So is Aegolism (Payment for 3 resses yesterday).  Woot!<P>Aladain<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Brambodius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Peridots have to be the nicest res payment I ever receive. <P>If I am borderline busy and someone offered me peridots to res them I would be far more inclined.  Mostly because this person has obviously taken an interest in issues that clerics face before asking a cleric to take an interest in their issue (lack of a res).<P>Very nice.<P>Brambodius</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bodin Battlehealer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">46 CLR here and I donatane my stones when I get a higher res  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>CLR gotta take care of CLR!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cali</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dots would be lovely compensation for a rez.  Though my favorite thing to receive is a 10dose SoW potion.<P> <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"><P>I love to rez shaman!<P>------------------<BR>~Calimayrn Anam'Cara<BR>Vicar of Tunare<BR>~Calizana Rhinelander<BR>Floating Barbarian Champion<BR>~Nyramilac<BR>17th Blade Sneaky Inky <BR><A HREF="http://www.lostorder.com" TARGET=_blank>Lost Order of Akalabeth</A><BR>Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Derenath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">That's what I answer if asked what I "charge" for a res: 210p or 20 peridots. I'm switching over to +giant in Velious and can't buy anywhere. Not having to find a port back to Antonica or Kunark to restock dots has saved me quite a bit of time. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaldaea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dots is a great form of payment.  Easy to carry around then cash and clerics are always running short on supply.  I always accept dot donation and usually have to refuse cash since it can get to be too heavy.<P>------------------<BR>Chaldaea DeBebylon - Samsara</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Guidar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">peridots are a clerics' best friend  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Guid</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tyggon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">One of my best rez donations has been a stack of peridots from a nice necro. Would have been happy with 5 peridots too, though.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tundar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bleh, double post, please ignore this.<p>[This message has been edited by Tundar (edited 06-04-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tundar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dots is THE way to pay a cleric for rezzing  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> And they are alot less weight than plat.<BR>That and 10 dose SoW potions, although I would take dots over a potion anyday.<P>If I get asked "how many dots?" I usually charge 5 (although I seldom charge).</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ceyria Vixx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Derenath, <P>Once you get your faction to dubious with King Tormax faction (assumably the last faction you'll raise unless you are Dain killing), you can purchase peridots in Kael. They are on a vendor in one of the rooms to either side of the long room full of the armor quest guys. <P>My problem, I'm level 39 and they don't sell jasper.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
